                            <comment id="12895805" author="ssc" created="Thu, 5 Aug 2010 22:06:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a first patch that changes invocations of Filesystem.get(conf) to Filesystem.get(path.toUri(), conf).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12895810" author="ssc" created="Thu, 5 Aug 2010 22:16:05 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think you are missing a slash in the URI:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s3:/testingbucket-12345/tmp/prePartialMultiply2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What happens if you try:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s3://testingbucket-12345/tmp/prePartialMultiply2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Andrew&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi Andrew,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I only specified the input path of the job (did that correctly with s3:// at the beginning) and the pathes for the M/R jobs executed before the &quot;partialMultiply&quot; worked correctly. I guess it must have to do something with the fact that this path contains two comma-separated URLs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know why there&apos;s only one slash in the stracktrace, maybe that was a typo from me as I had to change the real name of the bucket before posting here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12896382" author="ssc" created="Sun, 8 Aug 2010 17:21:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Found one more location where we have to use FileSystem.get(path.toUri(), conf)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
